Poland
October 8th 2020

"From Saturday, October 10, the new list will include 32 poviats and 6 cities that will enter the red zone. A very important change - the whole country will be included in the yellow zone, excluding poviats belonging to the red zone.
The new list of counties, which is valid from October 10

Red zone:

Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship: Aleksandrów poviat and Grudziądz;

Lubelskie Voivodeship: Janowski, Łęczyński and Włodawski poviats;

Łódź Voivodeship: Bełchatów, Wieluński and Piotrków Trybunalski poviats;

Lesser Poland Voivodeship: Limanowa, Myślenice, Nowy Targ, Suski and Tatra Poviats;

Mazowieckie voivodship: Otwock and Szydłowiec poviat;

Opolskie Voivodeship: Oleski Poviat;

Podkarpackie voivodship: Dębicki and Mielecki poviats;

Podlaskie voivodeship: Białystok, Zambrów and Suwałki poviats;

Pomorskie voivodship: Kartuski, Kościerzyna, Puck, Słupsk poviats and Sopot;

Silesia Province: Kłobuck County;

Świętokrzyskie Province: Kielce County and Kielce;

Warmińsko-Mazurskie voivodship: Bartoszyce, Działdowo, Iławski and Ostróda poviats;

Greater Poland Voivodeship: Krotoszyn, Międzychodzki, Rawicki and Wolsztyn poviats;

West Pomeranian Voivodeship: Koszalin."

